# HEARTBEAT.md — Health Check & Self-Monitoring

> Configures the bot's periodic self-monitoring behavior.
> The heartbeat system runs on a schedule and verifies system health.

---

## Heartbeat Configuration

- **Interval:** Every 15 minutes
- **Model:** `openrouter/minimax/minimax-m2.5:free` (zero cost)
- **Timeout:** 30 seconds per check
- **Alert Channel:** `#ops-alerts` (Slack channel for health notifications)

---

## Health Checks

### 1. LLM Connectivity
- **Check:** Send a minimal prompt to the primary LLM provider
- **Pass:** Response received within 10 seconds
- **Fail action:** Switch to fallback provider, alert in #ops-alerts

### 2. Slack Connection
- **Check:** Verify Socket Mode WebSocket is connected
- **Pass:** WebSocket state is OPEN
- **Fail action:** Attempt reconnect (max 3 retries), alert if persistent

### 3. MCP Server (n8n)
- **Check:** GET `http://localhost:5678/healthz`
- **Pass:** HTTP 200 response
- **Fail action:** Alert in #ops-alerts, disable MCP-dependent tools temporarily

### 4. Disk Usage
- **Check:** Workspace directory disk usage
- **Pass:** Below 80% capacity
- **Warn:** 80-90% — alert to clean up old sessions
- **Fail:** Above 90% — alert immediately, pause non-critical operations

### 5. Memory Usage
- **Check:** Node.js process heap usage
- **Pass:** Below 1.5 GB
- **Warn:** 1.5-1.8 GB — alert, trigger session compaction
- **Fail:** Above 1.8 GB — alert, graceful restart recommended

---

## Self-Check Prompt

When the heartbeat runs, use this minimal prompt:

```
System status check. Report:
1. Current time (UTC)
2. Active sessions count
3. Last error (if any in past 15 min)
4. Memory usage estimate
Respond in under 50 tokens.
```

---

## Alert Format

When posting to #ops-alerts:

```
:warning: **OpenClaw Health Alert**
• Check: [check name]
• Status: [WARN/FAIL]
• Detail: [what happened]
• Action: [what was done automatically]
• Needs human: [yes/no]
• Timestamp: [ISO 8601]
```

---

## Maintenance Windows

During scheduled maintenance, suppress non-critical alerts:

- **Weekly maintenance:** Sundays 2:00-4:00 AM ET
- **Suppress:** Disk and memory warnings
- **Keep active:** LLM and Slack connectivity checks

---

## Escalation

| Severity | Response | Notify |
|---|---|---|
| Info | Log only | Nobody |
| Warn | Post to #ops-alerts | On-call admin |
| Fail | Post to #ops-alerts + DM admin | Lorenz (admin) |
| Critical | Post + DM + attempt auto-recovery | Lorenz (admin) |
